<TITLE>Saints Row Showdown: 1 vs 2</TITLE>


<TEXT>
by  andri_g   
Hello again, friends! 
 
As a follow-up to my recent Saints Row games reviews, I <EVENT eid="e1" class="I_STATE">figured</EVENT> that I would <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE">compare</EVENT> the first two games--when the series was still <EVENT eid="e3" class="I_ACTION">trying</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">position</EVENT> itself as a GTA-style game, before it <EVENT eid="e5" class="I_STATE">started</EVENT> doing it's own thing. 
 
Here are the <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">highlights</EVENT>, and lowlights, of Saints Row and Saints Row 2 and how these games <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE">compare</EVENT> to each other. 
 

 Saints Row  Pros:  characters  music  story  vehicles damage (progressive, realistic)  driving  jacking (being driven)  steering (solid)   Cons:  vehicle camera (no position lock)  locating   weapons aiming  ammunition    Saints Row 2  Pros:  characters creation  personalities   menu system  money (more, sooner)  music  story  vehicles crib garages  durability  <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE">locating</EVENT>  Septic Avenger activity   weapons <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">aiming</EVENT>  more ammo  purchaseable ammo   Cons:  character animations (too long, make controls unresponsive)  cheap deaths (too many)  checkpoint system (inconsistent)  vehicles steering (twitchy)  entry (often fails)  camera (no position lock--default aim too high)  Racing re-design  <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">jacking</EVENT> (being <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">driven</EVENT>; often fails)  extraction while <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">driving</EVENT>    

 Summary  
While Saints Row 2 has more pros than Saints Row, it also <EVENT eid="e13" class="STATE">has</EVENT> more cons. 
 
The original game is definitely more a driving fan's game. Its vehicle controls and responsiveness are better <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE">suited</EVENT> to gamers who <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE">like</EVENT> their vehicles to <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE">feel</EVENT> more like the real thing. Not to <EVENT eid="e17" class="REPORTING">say</EVENT> that the vehicle controls in Saints Row 2 don't <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE">work</EVENT>, but they do feel more arcade-like. 
 
By comparison, Saints Row 2 is more a shooter fan's game. The supply of guns and ammo is greater and, if you <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">run</EVENT> out, you have the option to <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">buy</EVENT> more (in the original, though, you can run-out of ammo completely). The accuracy of the weapons in Saints Row 2 also are much better for more bullets hitting their targets. 
 
Saints Row 2 looks better, but as an driving adventure game, Saints Row feels better. The story for Saints Row is a little more solid, but the shooting controls in Saints Row 2 are much better. Choose the game that best fits your play-style and you won't <EVENT eid="e21" class="STATE">go</EVENT> wrong. 
 
Thanks for <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE">reading</EVENT>; game on! 
